critical_positive: At first, I thought it was an interview. I went in 'blind' and was ready to answer whatever he asked me. Then, I realized it was just a conversation with a stranger. We talked about the differences between the United States and Canada, which was awesome. For example, the differences in our government and the handling of the Coronavirus. He was very kind and easygoing.
critical_negative: I would have to say that he certainly asked me a lot more questions than I asked him. I wish I would have seemed more interested in his life, because he seemed very interested in mine. Other than that, it seems that we worked well together and got along great.

rest_of_day_open: My week is almost ending so I see it going good, resting at home and buying essentials and taking care of necessities. critical_positive: The thing that worked well was that we conversed about things that interested us as individuals and didnt really care about what we were talking about. We were also having a good time and talking to upwards of 30 minutes so we were just enjoying the conversation overall which made the time fly.
critical_negative: The main thing that probably did not work would be how my conversation partner thought I was interviewing her but I was just another participant in the video conversation. Overall though we got past that and the conversation starting feeling like more of a conversation than how it initially started off.
